Diagnosis.
Males differing from congeners by slender and curving ET pointing smoothly distad at its distal end (
Fig. 29c
) and dRTA with a ventral bulge (
Figs 29a, b
); epigyne with two large triangular processes at posterior margine of lateral lobes (LL) (
Fig. 30a
) [see also diagnosis for 

jaegeri

species group above].

Palp.
As in diagnosis with cymbium more than twice as long as tibia (
Fig. 29b
), dRTA beak-like and vRTA wide and triangular in ventral view (
Fig. 29a
); ET retrolaterad with distal tip bent at right angle (
Fig. 29c
).

Epigyne/vulva.
As in diagnosis with MS enlarged, roundish and bulged outward ventrally (
Fig. 30a
), CD massive and dark in colour and fully to partially sclerotized (
Fig. 30b
), GP reduced in size and situated close to TL (
Figs 30c, d
).
